Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.59,0:02:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this thing on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.71,0:02:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Questions about, we had some questions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.09,0:02:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,about the spiritual warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.78,0:02:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,As we evolve up through the various archetypes,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.25,0:02:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Jung talked about the archetypes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.18,0:02:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, we're the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.61,0:02:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual world is wondrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.81,0:02:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We go to the New Age festival
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.86,0:02:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're just blown away with it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.05,0:02:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we get more serious, we get more aligned,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.09,0:02:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we get more power, we give up the adolescent,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.19,0:02:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and we become dedicated to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.12,0:03:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of dedication arises the spiritual warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.47,0:03:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual warrior, as it expresses itself
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in these classes, is extreme dedication
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.47,0:03:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to the truth no matter what,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.06,0:03:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to die for the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.68,0:03:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to give up all positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.34,0:03:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called devotional non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.62,0:03:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so in the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.87,0:03:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual warrior starts from his solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.91,0:03:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows what's right and he's willing to kill the infidel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.21,0:03:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He can kill the infidel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of the jihad people are in their spiritual warrior,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.88,0:03:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,energized by their spleen, unfortunately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.52,0:03:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,To kill the enemy out of hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.87,0:03:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is a totally different karmic consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.06,0:03:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,than doing it out of one's dedication to principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:04:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more evolved spiritual warrior
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.50,0:04:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is the archetype within you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.09,0:04:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,which becomes dedicated to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.99,0:04:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a warrior to truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ was a warrior for truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.18,0:04:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I brought a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.97,0:04:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not bring you peace on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.52,0:04:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but peace in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.71,0:04:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not bring you peace on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.80,0:04:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.58,0:04:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They deleted idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.99,0:04:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But I got the original and it said idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.06,0:04:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,To have any impact on mankind, you gotta be real.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta know where mankind is living.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.69,0:04:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak to where we all live, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.56,0:04:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We all live where it's real, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.61,0:04:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We talk from the intellect and spot all this fancy stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.66,0:04:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but where we live is the real.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.45,0:04:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And on a certain level, everybody knows the real.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.06,0:04:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We discovered, for instance, which,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.77,0:04:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that's this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.01,0:04:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to shock you with that one this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.06,0:05:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.75,0:05:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we don't want to shock you with that one, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.97,0:05:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then the warrior,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.60,0:05:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he comes up out of the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.98,0:05:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and stops being confrontational,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and he moves into his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.26,0:05:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have the,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.14,0:05:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the warrior who also has a heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.70,0:05:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That pretty much represents the U.S. position right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's a very ferocious and fearsome
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.81,0:05:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and very powerful warrior, it also has a heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.50,0:05:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right behind the guns is the food for the populace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.44,0:05:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.64,0:05:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Who ever heard of a warrior doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.32,0:05:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragging a wagon load of grub for the,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.72,0:05:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,for the evil ones out there, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.99,0:05:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, so America has more evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.18,0:05:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a heart about the whole thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.99,0:05:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he begins to speak of the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.81,0:05:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the warrior moves from warrior to a higher level,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.23,0:06:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because the archetype of the warrior
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.49,0:06:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the highest of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.26,0:06:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is the phase of the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.75,0:06:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the warrior can also be,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.08,0:06:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of the warrior is the denouncer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.93,0:06:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the polarizer, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.16,0:06:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, once you speak for the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that's different than demeaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.19,0:06:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who disagree with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.67,0:06:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So to vilify the president because you disagree with him
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.98,0:06:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is not integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.74,0:06:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To say you disagree with him, that is integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.97,0:06:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But to vilify him is a fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.47,0:06:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't vilify Bin Laden.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.70,0:06:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't vilify Saddam Hussein.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.29,0:06:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,These are people that are run by energies
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.29,0:06:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of which they have no awareness whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.94,0:06:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no awareness of what is running them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.75,0:06:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, intrinsically, everyone is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.50,0:06:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What enables you to face the truth, you know, is, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.80,0:07:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of things is the devotion to the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.91,0:07:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because the fastest way to God is through truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.12,0:07:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the fast way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.58,0:07:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,One has to be devoted, so devotion brings in the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.31,0:07:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Zen-like exactitude
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.74,0:07:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of the devotion to God and truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.33,0:07:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.33,0:07:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It can look ferocious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.83,0:07:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It is ferocious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.38,0:07:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an enormous compassion then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.29,0:07:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of compassion, one can see the downside,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.44,0:07:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the mistaken side of the kamikaze pilot or the shoe bomber.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.64,0:07:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The shoe bomber, God bless him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.92,0:08:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the idiot child, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.17,0:08:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's doing his bit for the cause,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.82,0:08:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,getting on a plane with his shoes loaded with bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.26,0:08:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God bless it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.58,0:08:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.11,0:08:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.89,0:08:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason that you have to take surgical action quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.89,0:08:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, talking as a pragmatist,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,after all, I'm a physician,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.82,0:08:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and I see things as a physician sees things,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.69,0:08:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the dangers to the world have become more,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.91,0:08:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the dangers to the world are more than they ever were
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.85,0:08:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because of amplification.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of amplification, a mad dog who used to be a weirdo
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.10,0:08:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that lived out in a trailer camp someplace and he looked weird,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.33,0:08:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and when he came to town, everybody thought he was a weirdo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.35,0:08:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowadays, he has access to enormously powerful weapons,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.69,0:09:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,not just a little harmless weirdo anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.36,0:09:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The deviant politics that comes through
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.86,0:09:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through philosophical distortion used to be some guy ranting
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.16,0:09:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and raving in the bar and you all figured he's a local nut.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.30,0:09:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, now he's on international television and he's talking
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.90,0:09:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to six million people at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.92,0:09:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it is now far more important to detect,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood early in the game, early in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.94,0:09:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's one of the things that propelled, I'm sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.86,0:09:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,our administration to take action is because the capacity to deal
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.42,0:09:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in nuclear weapons is so enormously powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.30,0:09:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to huge numbers of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.00,0:09:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just fool around with these people anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.71,0:09:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just say he's a local nut.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.03,0:09:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just ignore him because he's carrying bombs
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.73,0:10:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's carrying nuclear weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.39,0:10:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't just say, well, he's a local nut.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.10,0:10:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just say he's a local nut.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.13,0:10:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just dismiss the purveyors of falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.89,0:10:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,as harmless nuts who are carried away by mistaken enthusiasms
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.90,0:10:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're influencing the opinion of millions of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.79,0:10:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So amplification then means that falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.70,0:10:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way is more dangerous than it ever was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.99,0:10:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood is more dangerous than it ever was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.12,0:10:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It has always had a high price.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.07,0:10:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Denial is falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.17,0:10:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You say if you don't learn from history,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.17,0:10:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you're condemned to repeat it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.98,0:10:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I use some historical examples
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.41,0:10:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're not so polarized about history
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.50,0:10:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,as we are about current events.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.05,0:10:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look at past history with a little more cool head
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.79,0:10:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and not get your solar plexus all in an uproar
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.70,0:10:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,over current events.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.09,0:11:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If we looked, you know, my generation was World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So after World War I, the espionage system
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.52,0:11:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States, the intelligence system,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.87,0:11:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,reported constantly to the Secretary of State.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.12,0:11:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And every morning, the Secretary of State got a report
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,from the intelligence departments.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.83,0:11:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,After World War I, Secretary of State Stimson was appointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.85,0:11:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,When Stimson took office, they served him up on his first day
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.41,0:11:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as Secretary of State with the intelligence report,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.25,0:11:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which kept track of the Japanese especially.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.53,0:11:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said these fateful words, gentlemen do not read other
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.10,0:11:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,gentleman's mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.10,0:11:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That cost us Pearl Harbor and millions of men
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.25,0:11:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because the intelligence was, I learned it from my,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.52,0:12:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned it in grade school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.47,0:12:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My teacher said Japan with a swarming population like that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.52,0:12:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and lack of, what do you call it, rubber tires, oils,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.74,0:12:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all that, what do you call that, whatever it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.36,0:12:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to have to expand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.79,0:12:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.57,0:12:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever thinks of controlling the population,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.73,0:12:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way, in which you wouldn't have any shortage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.91,0:12:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.39,0:12:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It demands proclivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what, we have a constantly expanding population
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that is straining everything in every direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.37,0:12:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So Stimson played by the rules that we,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.22,0:12:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that the doctor and I did this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.17,0:12:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, gentlemen do not read other gentleman's mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.22,0:12:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So intelligence reports to the State Department,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.75,0:12:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which were rife with all the intelligence
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.84,0:12:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Japan was preparing for, were completely ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.35,0:12:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And the results were Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.46,0:13:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,America is always being surprised, surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.60,0:13:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always surprised by Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.51,0:13:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,surprised by the Bay of Pigs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.29,0:13:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Surprised, people are always being surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way you get to be surprised is to be stupid, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have your head in the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.77,0:13:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're surprised when somebody gooses you .
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.47,0:13:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He was surprised when kids...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.62,0:13:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, so beware of people that are surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.10,0:13:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't live long on the streets ofines.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.62,0:13:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Change often.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.83,0:13:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,New York City, being surprised, friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.42,0:13:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember walking at midnight
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.16,0:13:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on 10th Avenue,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.76,0:13:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and I heard the footsteps
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.08,0:13:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,behind me. It's like one in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.24,0:13:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of the footsteps,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.82,0:13:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew what was on their mind, and what
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they intended, and who they were,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.63,0:13:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,without turning around. It would have been
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.20,0:13:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a mistake to turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.32,0:13:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have your antenna up, you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,survive. Okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.12,0:14:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to be virtuous and holier than thou, you've got
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.12,0:14:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive so you can get on TV and be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.98,0:14:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,virtuous and holier than thou.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.52,0:14:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So somebody's got to protect your butt while
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.71,0:14:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you're mouthing off, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.92,0:14:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You need a realist somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.37,0:14:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's a realist? The realist
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.80,0:14:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then is willing to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.30,0:14:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,accept the downside of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.66,0:14:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,human life, because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.98,0:14:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he's compassionate towards it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.13,0:14:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not compassionate,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.20,0:14:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that means you're in a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.94,0:14:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,make-wrong, and if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.49,0:14:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in a make-wrong, you don't want to look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.69,0:14:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying? Compassion allows
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.61,0:14:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you to see that a lot of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.57,0:14:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that walk the planet will
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.37,0:14:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,skin you alive, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.08,0:14:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They will. And if
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.52,0:14:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you love them enough, you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.54,0:14:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that that is a fact. That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.49,0:14:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll skin you alive. We'll get to more
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.66,0:14:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of that this afternoon. This afternoon we're going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.62,0:14:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,business.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.02,0:15:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Skin you alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.86,0:15:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Where naivete,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.94,0:15:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of naivete
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.96,0:15:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,costs everybody their life savings
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.94,0:15:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and retirement accounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.84,0:15:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All the old folks are working
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.84,0:15:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,at Walmarts right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.62,0:15:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The 401k
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.29,0:15:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,went west.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.65,0:15:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll talk about that this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You see then that love
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.17,0:15:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,opens the door to the awareness of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.29,0:15:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, because you don't have to take
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.12,0:15:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a positionality. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.61,0:15:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,care for people
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.21,0:15:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what they might be,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.35,0:15:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because you see that that's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.04,0:15:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,only where they've evolved to at this point
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.07,0:15:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of time. They've only
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.37,0:15:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved to the point. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.28,0:15:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the people who are the mad bombers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.69,0:15:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,are in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.71,0:15:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,spleen of their
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.09,0:15:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual warrior. A dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.80,0:15:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,place to be. A very dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.71,0:15:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,place to be. Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.95,0:16:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,they're very dangerous people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.87,0:16:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And to turn your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.17,0:16:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,back to them and think that a prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.22,0:16:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,vigil is going to stop and they ain't going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.42,0:16:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So what can we all do as
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.00,0:16:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,individuals? We can all be
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.35,0:16:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,champions of the truth. We can all come
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.25,0:16:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,out of denial. And we
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.34,0:16:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,can all evolve ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.34,0:16:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually as best we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.62,0:16:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're talking about the spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.80,0:16:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We've talked about truth as
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,descriptive in form,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.41,0:16:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which is content, but
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.61,0:16:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that content is with an overall field
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.69,0:16:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,called context.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.12,0:16:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as a statement,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.20,0:16:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a verifiable statement of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.89,0:16:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that ignores context.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.15,0:16:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how all the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacies that run this world arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.71,0:16:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.66,0:16:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but not in this context, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.52,0:16:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in this context.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.92,0:17:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Our devotion to truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.12,0:17:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,then, because truth is the expression
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.85,0:17:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of God. God's expression
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.30,0:17:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,within the realm of human knowability
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.25,0:17:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is via truth
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.33,0:17:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and via love,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.11,0:17:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,right? Via compassion,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.22,0:17:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,via understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.53,0:17:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and benevolence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.10,0:17:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.99,0:17:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,wage war in as benevolent
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.34,0:17:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a style as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.30,0:17:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all you can say for the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.17,0:17:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot different than a war we've all
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.19,0:17:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,lived through, or a lot of us older have lived through,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.13,0:17:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,where it was done out of vengeance and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.02,0:17:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred. That was a whole different energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.91,0:17:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Vengeance and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.31,0:17:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not done out of vengeance and hatred,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.18,0:17:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,although some of the aftermath of 9-11
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.18,0:17:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is vengeance and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.88,0:17:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty much
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.31,0:17:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,mellowed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.09,0:17:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, 9-11 let loose
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.61,0:17:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the dogs of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.44,0:17:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,9-11 let loose the dogs of war
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.64,0:18:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and changed the game forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us are going to just hop
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.42,0:18:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,on a plane anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.64,0:18:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the rest of our lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.77,0:18:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to stand in line
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.20,0:18:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and have our tick off our shoes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.14,0:18:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, oh, that mad
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.60,0:18:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,shoe bomber. He really
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,screwed us up. I'm glad
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.51,0:18:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I wear Dr. Scholl's because
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.22,0:18:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I can zip them open, put my shoes back
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.50,0:18:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,on like that. And the other kind
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.30,0:18:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of people have to do their shoelaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.97,0:18:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're black shoes, of course, with shoelaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.70,0:18:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get to the black shoelaces
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.51,0:18:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,people this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.00,0:18:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They're either businessmen or FBI. You know that right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.72,0:18:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I never trust anybody with black
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.40,0:18:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,lace-up shoes, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.40,0:18:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The afternoon good, one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.33,0:18:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.03,0:18:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world, then, to be
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.90,0:19:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,mistaken is more dangerous than
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.81,0:19:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,ever. It's more dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.75,0:19:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.77,0:19:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,effects are so amplified
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.25,0:19:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by electronic communication,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by proliferations
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.92,0:19:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in science,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.84,0:19:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,bomb making,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.42,0:19:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera, has become
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.68,0:19:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody in his backyard
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.63,0:19:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,can brew up some
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.89,0:19:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,germs that'll kill off millions of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.25,0:19:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,people. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.59,0:19:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't allow
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.29,0:19:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,people to be as deviant as you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.09,0:19:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The mad guy in the bar, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.65,0:19:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,his only dangerousness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.73,0:19:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was he'd get behind the car and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.60,0:19:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,kill somebody on the way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the mad person now can
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.51,0:19:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with a little chemistry
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.24,0:19:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,set, stir up enough germs
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.20,0:19:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to kill half of the people in this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.33,0:19:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,planet. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.42,0:19:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we can't allow deviance
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.09,0:19:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and negativity to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.66,0:19:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,reach the point of dangerousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.93,0:20:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We're too close to the ruptured
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.02,0:20:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,appendix now. You've got to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.25,0:20:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,operate a little earlier in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.28,0:20:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Better to make a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.78,0:20:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and take out a healthy appendix once in a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.65,0:20:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,while than to lose
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.45,0:20:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a teenage girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.86,0:20:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the surgeon gets
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.63,0:20:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,criticized. Well, we looked at it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.73,0:20:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in pathology and there was nothing wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with that appendix. It was really
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.25,0:20:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,mesenteric adenitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.81,0:20:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the time, it sure looked like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.74,0:20:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,appendicitis. So, what's the guy going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.51,0:20:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he takes a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.16,0:20:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,risk that he gets criticized
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.74,0:20:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has to go before
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.88,0:20:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the hospital board to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.79,0:20:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,how come you took out
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.27,0:20:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a healthy appendix. Well, he didn't think
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.27,0:20:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a healthy appendix, but he didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.82,0:20:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,want to take a chance. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.08,0:20:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the margin of error now, in a way,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.04,0:20:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is less than it used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.54,0:20:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The margin of error. Everything moves
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.69,0:20:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,much faster because of the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.30,0:20:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is amplified.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.84,0:20:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, error as well as truth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.56,0:20:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,gets quickly amplified.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.27,0:21:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's quickly amplified, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.35,0:21:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,our own spiritual work has a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.09,0:21:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,greater impact. And as
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.59,0:21:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we mentioned before, when we were
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.46,0:21:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about going
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.50,0:21:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from the linear to the non-linear, from
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.50,0:21:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian science
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.50,0:21:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.95,0:21:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and beyond,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.65,0:21:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you saw that each
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.78,0:21:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,choice that you make then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.71,0:21:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,collapses the wave function, speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.78,0:21:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.80,0:21:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and reinforces
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.30,0:21:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.07,0:21:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Reinforces the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.48,0:21:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.68,0:21:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.09,0:21:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,your own integrity in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.20,0:21:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,striving for truth raises
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.55,0:21:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of all of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.57,0:21:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind. And that which
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.92,0:21:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,makes falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.85,0:21:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,weaker instead of stronger
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.74,0:21:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is the prevalence
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.94,0:21:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of the consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.96,0:21:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.64,0:21:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level now at
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.38,0:22:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,207 is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.64,0:22:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,surface that which is negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.38,0:22:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand? As you move
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.51,0:22:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,from 190, which was non-integral,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.75,0:22:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to 180, which is non-integral,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.25,0:22:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to the non-integral, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.48,0:22:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.80,0:22:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.93,0:22:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.93,0:22:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.16,0:22:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.16,0:22:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.53,0:22:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.53,0:22:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to jump the story of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.53,0:22:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,business, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.53,0:22:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what I was taught, I
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.53,0:22:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,remember a sales guy who was trying
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.53,0:22:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to get me to sell peanut vending
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.53,0:22:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,machines. Did I tell you my peanut
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.53,0:22:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,vending machine story?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.53,0:22:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really this afternoon's
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.53,0:22:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,story, but would you give me a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.53,0:22:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,little preview?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.84,0:22:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I had 1,001 jobs, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.84,0:22:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,1,001 jobs. People think they're
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.84,0:22:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,underpaid now. I worked as an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.84,0:22:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,intern 100 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.84,0:22:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 400 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.84,0:22:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 400 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.84,0:22:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 400 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.84,0:22:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 400 hours a month for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.84,0:22:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,$100 a month, so that's a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.84,0:22:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,quarter an hour, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.84,0:22:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, in the summertime,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.84,0:22:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to find a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.84,0:22:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, in the summertime, you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.80,0:22:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,had to find a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.80,0:22:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, in the summertime, you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.80,0:22:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,had to find a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.80,0:22:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So here was this ad to be a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.80,0:22:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,sales representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.80,0:22:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the job
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.09,0:22:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So here was this ad to be a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.09,0:22:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,sales representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.09,0:22:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the job was you work for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.09,0:22:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,this sales guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.09,0:22:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.09,0:22:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He checks in a hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.09,0:22:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You meet him in this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.13,0:22:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives you the pitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.13,0:23:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The pitch is you get these
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.13,0:23:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,retired farmers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.13,0:23:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,retirement money,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.13,0:23:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get them to invest in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.13,0:23:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,peanut vending machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.13,0:23:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.13,0:23:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.27,0:23:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.27,0:23:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.88,0:23:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.88,0:23:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.88,0:23:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.88,0:23:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.88,0:23:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.88,0:23:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.88,0:23:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.88,0:23:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.88,0:23:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.88,0:23:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.88,0:23:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.88,0:23:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.88,0:23:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.35,0:23:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.51,0:23:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.51,0:23:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.51,0:23:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.51,0:23:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.51,0:23:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.51,0:23:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.51,0:23:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.51,0:23:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.16,0:23:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.16,0:23:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.16,0:23:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.16,0:23:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.50,0:23:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.50,0:23:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.67,0:23:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.67,0:23:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of honesty and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.88,0:23:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I brought this up, and he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.00,0:23:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, that's really not right to fool these guys
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.55,0:23:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,out of their retirement when you know
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.92,0:23:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not going to be emptying every week or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.90,0:23:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, if you don't get their money, somebody else will.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.96,0:24:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.68,0:24:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the world of the 30s or 40s.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.20,0:24:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.63,0:24:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the prevailing level of consciousness was 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.47,0:24:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 190, business was business.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.71,0:24:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And ethics was ethics.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.95,0:24:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't miss the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.42,0:24:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't get their money, somebody will.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.18,0:24:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There you got the rationalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.81,0:24:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So nonintegrity survives by virtue of rationalization,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.90,0:24:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,making it sound OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.40,0:24:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But truth cuts through that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.94,0:24:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So my intuition told me that I really
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.81,0:24:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't have the heart to take people's retirement money.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.40,0:24:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At death's door, you're going to be reviewing your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.11,0:24:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll be looking at all these poor old guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.11,0:24:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll take the retirement money.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.51,0:24:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I really didn't want to look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.64,0:24:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So people now that are dedicated to spiritual truth
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.83,0:25:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,have a great impact on the collective consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.94,0:25:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind, because it went from 190 to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.04,0:25:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, 207 is a whole new ballgame.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.25,0:25:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At 207, nonintegrity begins to surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.44,0:25:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,like the good begins to drive out the bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.50,0:25:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So at 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.24,0:25:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how we conduct a war, even in a world that's at 207,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.48,0:25:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,although the US is at 431.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.53,0:25:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to, as ambiguous as it may sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.33,0:25:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we try to conduct an ethical war.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.71,0:25:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,An ethical war.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.63,0:25:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,As ethical as you can make it, surgical precision.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.79,0:25:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to be benevolent at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.09,0:25:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Snare the Komodo dragon before it kills any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.07,0:25:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is the moral.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.10,0:25:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say the moral predicament of the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.84,0:26:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way I see the US handling it at the present time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.93,0:26:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is best it can with an unpleasant condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.05,0:26:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, has anybody got any questions about war and peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.85,0:26:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing as we just straightened out Sun Tzu, who
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.28,0:26:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote The Art of War?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.80,0:26:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The classic is The Art of War by Sun Tzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.51,0:26:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Art of War.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.92,0:26:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an art form.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.18,0:26:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.81,0:26:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I like this title, The Art of War.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.34,0:26:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The Art of War.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.46,0:26:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how it looks at it as a game board.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.30,0:26:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody had a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.09,0:26:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.59,0:26:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a few more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.51,0:26:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we're going to have lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.96,0:26:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And then this afternoon, I want to do business, science,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.29,0:26:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other areas of human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.33,0:26:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can stand up and speak, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.68,0:26:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.93,0:26:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.75,0:27:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They're both the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.42,0:27:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.70,0:27:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, from here down, what you're really talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.66,0:27:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,are negative energies, which classically, theologically,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.16,0:27:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,religiously, spiritually, have been called either Luciferic
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.14,0:27:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or Satanic or demonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.68,0:27:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.57,0:27:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, non-truth, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.33,0:27:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are just different qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.29,0:27:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Satanic has been, it takes two forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.34,0:27:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Our society is attacked by both ends, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.02,0:27:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The Satanic takes the form of bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.95,0:27:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing, murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.67,0:27:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate Satanic energy is the serial child killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.82,0:27:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrates around seven, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.76,0:27:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The pornographic addict child killer
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.82,0:27:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates probably the lowest of all, around seven
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.10,0:27:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.91,0:28:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with cruelty, savagery.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.15,0:28:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw it in Nanking in the 30s.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.48,0:28:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,30,000 innocent civilians slaughtered, raped, murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.05,0:28:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.02,0:28:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It preys upon the weak and the innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.73,0:28:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, oh, while we're talking about ethics,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.65,0:28:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it is unethical and non-integrous to tempt people
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.18,0:28:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,with weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.47,0:28:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,To purposely place temptation in front of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.95,0:28:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you must handle the karmic consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.58,0:28:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a new maid to clean your house,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.84,0:28:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you leave a pile of cash sitting out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.92,0:28:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who is the perpetrator?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.59,0:28:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And who is the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.19,0:28:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.94,0:28:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.40,0:28:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're provoking human weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.48,0:28:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead us not into temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.92,0:28:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So to lead people into temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.90,0:29:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So weakness leads people into temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.44,0:29:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,To be in denial makes you a choice, plump little victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.43,0:29:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I hadn't had paranoid alertness,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.89,0:29:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have got mugged on 10th Avenue that night,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.25,0:29:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other times in New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.11,0:29:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can't be into denial, because that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.85,0:29:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you the provocateur by virtue of the temptation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.44,0:29:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and attraction of weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.75,0:29:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the predator-prey response.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.77,0:29:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why weakness does not work
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.72,0:29:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in international politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.00,0:29:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Weakness just pulls forth the predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.57,0:29:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He just can't resist the fact that you've
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.57,0:29:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,got all that money, all that vulnerability sitting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.33,0:29:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to take moral responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.03,0:29:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that you tempted the predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.92,0:29:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So the victim doesn't stop being victim
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.70,0:29:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,until the victim takes responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.96,0:29:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for the part they play.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.58,0:30:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to go jogging at midnight in Central Park,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.22,0:30:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to take responsibility that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.05,0:30:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a luscious little victim that is going
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.33,0:30:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to be beyond the self-control of half-drunken or intoxicated
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.74,0:30:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,people with no sense of honor or ethics.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.50,0:30:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to get raped no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.50,0:30:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.90,0:30:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If not tonight, tomorrow night, sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.33,0:30:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see that weakness then has a moral downside to it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.51,0:30:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you are tempting those who are weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.44,0:30:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how do we know they're weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.75,0:30:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.50,0:30:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're tempting 78% of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.25,0:30:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulnerability and weakness tempts 78% of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.53,0:30:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,78% of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.55,0:30:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.66,0:30:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rest of the population is not
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.16,0:30:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in peace, ethics, or honor,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.98,0:30:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,unless it's a pop political slogan.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.35,0:31:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the peace movement is not about peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.59,0:31:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.01,0:31:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, it's using peace as a slogan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.86,0:31:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, it denigrates the true meaning of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.50,0:31:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which is peaceful does not denigrate,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.44,0:31:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,does not marginalize people.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.22,0:31:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is contentious.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.16,0:31:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Contentious is not peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.01,0:31:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace does not come out of contention.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.92,0:31:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What comes out of contention?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.74,0:31:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,War comes out of contention.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.01,0:31:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you make peace contentious, you're declaring war.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.56,0:31:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To declare war in the name of peace is lucifer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.48,0:31:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how you take what sounds like truth
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.20,0:31:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and you turn it into its opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.29,0:31:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You polarize the people in a contentious war of ideology,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.83,0:31:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,power politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.98,0:31:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.42,0:31:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.46,0:31:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.67,0:31:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.73,0:31:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.97,0:31:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.02,0:31:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.13,0:31:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.19,0:31:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it divides people.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.43,0:32:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That which divides people into war and camps
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.23,0:32:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,does not represent peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.65,0:32:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which is peace unites people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.21,0:32:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So 78% of the population, then, is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.19,0:32:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,run by what we call dark energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.45,0:32:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Those on the right-hand side are called, in politics,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.83,0:32:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,keep the calibrated level up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.18,0:32:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In politics, we call the far right fascist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.07,0:32:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The far right is fascist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.38,0:32:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The far left is Marxist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.38,0:32:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The far right is fascist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.25,0:32:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The far right is cruel, fascistic, and dictatorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.92,0:32:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's savage.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.01,0:32:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's merciless.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.59,0:32:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's without compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.33,0:32:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In China right now, to even voice certain things
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.01,0:32:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,gets you not only arrested, but executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.01,0:32:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.29,0:32:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as in Arabic countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.85,0:32:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Even do or say certain things brings
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.55,0:32:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic, instant execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.91,0:33:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.41,0:33:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about lawyers, martial law.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.13,0:33:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It precludes all those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.73,0:33:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So the far right is fascistic, sadistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.25,0:33:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Another aspect of the satanic, which
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.24,0:33:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,may not look the same to you, has
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.00,0:33:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to do with sexuality, sexual perversion, sexual obsession,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.00,0:33:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,drugs, the kind of music put out by certain groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.60,0:33:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Kick your pregnant wife in the belly, hate rock, and obscenity.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.50,0:33:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Great names celebrated by the media are overtly profane,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.49,0:33:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,overtly sacrilegious, overtly, overtly attack
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.24,0:34:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is sacred, that which is divine, that which is holy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.05,0:34:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.99,0:34:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That which attracts the satanic is innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.71,0:34:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Innocence in our culture is youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.53,0:34:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's very easy to program youth with programs that respect
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.71,0:34:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or decency, is being white, is being uncool.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.01,0:34:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The contempt for that which is holy and sacred comes out of the satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.23,0:34:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the satanic attacking our culture via the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.23,0:34:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The main avenue of the satanic attack is via the media,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.96,0:34:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in which many of these musical things calibrate 70 or 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.44,0:34:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, this week, I was at a concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.19,0:34:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I was at a concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.34,0:34:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The media announced a new video game.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.19,0:34:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.96,0:34:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop your guard, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.94,0:35:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.21,0:35:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called Postal 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.17,0:35:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Postal 2 is worse than Postal 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.28,0:35:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Postal 2 and 1 is worse than, what's that name, auto something?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.51,0:35:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Grand Theft Auto, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.73,0:35:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Grand Theft Auto is bad enough, but Postal is trying to win the game of seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.42,0:35:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,how depraved can you get.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.78,0:35:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what Postal calibrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.53,0:35:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to calibrate in front of this audience, Postal, a video game, which is over 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.05,0:35:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there is an innocent game, which is programming your unconscious at a calibrated level of 30,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.61,0:35:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which is contempt for all that is decent, holy, or integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.03,0:36:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Savagery at its extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.34,0:36:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.36,0:36:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have satanic in the political realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.28,0:36:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fascism.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.28,0:36:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We have it in the realm of the lower, what do we call it, the bottom of the barrel of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.46,0:36:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Drug addiction, savagery, murder, pimps, prostitutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.53,0:36:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Pimps don't do very well calibration-wise either.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.55,0:36:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They do about 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.88,0:36:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I said 30?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.76,0:36:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.67,0:36:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Said sadism.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.15,0:36:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They like to beat up the girls, you know, and savage them, terrify them, stab them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.40,0:36:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They get out of line.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.34,0:36:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So you got six girls in your stable, one gets out, you cut her eyes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.75,0:36:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That scares the crap out of everybody on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.34,0:36:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that, they do what the hell you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.82,0:36:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, I once treated a pimp back in the East, and I know the extent to which they go.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.78,0:37:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He would come in and say, God, I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.09,0:37:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You think beating up girls all night is easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.05,0:37:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You should try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.69,0:37:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He's trying for my sympathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.21,0:37:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,These girls have forced him, forced him, they forced him to do this, is the way he looks at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.15,0:37:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She misbehaved.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.82,0:37:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What else could I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.82,0:37:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, can't keep this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.82,0:37:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so that's satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.46,0:37:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the Luciferic is something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.98,0:37:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the satanic can take you all the way down to seven, the serial child killer calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.05,0:37:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,at seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.05,0:37:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They're usually possessed from lower astral domains, and really not in a certain way,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.76,0:37:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not really responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.76,0:37:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the Luciferic is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.00,0:37:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Luciferic, what is Lucifer?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.32,0:37:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucifer's sin was pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.38,0:37:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Luciferic stands for the denial of the sovereignty of God, therefore it is the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.42,0:38:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,ultimate of arrogance and pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.21,0:38:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Luciferic is at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.84,0:38:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In our society, the far left calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.59,0:38:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The refusal to accept divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.53,0:38:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So that particular energy wants to wipe God out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.76,0:38:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In human society, and turn it into a secular society.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.69,0:38:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the reason our society calibrates as high as it does is the Constitution of the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.57,0:38:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,United States is over 700, because the rights and equality of all men are a result of the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.98,0:38:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledgement of the divinity of our creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.05,0:38:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we're equal is because we are created that way by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.76,0:38:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what makes 720.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.23,0:38:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Constitution of the United States is the highest.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.67,0:38:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's over 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.67,0:38:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.67,0:38:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,highest of any government on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.19,0:38:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Luciferic would like to remove any acknowledgement of God because Lucifer's pride
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.34,0:39:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,was he did not want to acknowledge that there was any power greater than him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.84,0:39:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Luciferic, to begin with, hates God and wants to remove any reminder of God in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.09,0:39:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,every place in America.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.13,0:39:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when Madeleine Murray wanted God removed as, I think it was prayer in the school,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.86,0:39:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't that prayer in the school?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.90,0:39:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She became the most hated, despised woman in America, and I saw a documentary on her
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.86,0:39:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,subsequent life, and it was abysmal, down to the trailer park, then down to degradation,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.78,0:39:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then down to murder and suicide in the family, and then family murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.59,0:39:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It was downhill.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.59,0:39:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, to say that, to destroy God is a different intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.90,0:39:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the energy of a thing comes out of its spiritual intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.84,0:39:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,To destroy God is to restore God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.86,0:40:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse to acknowledge the source of one's own existence, which is a Luciferic error.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.25,0:40:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To arrive at that, you have to do a great deal of alteration of philosophy, and so the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.57,0:40:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophical and ethical basis upon which these things rest are always gross distortions.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.28,0:40:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And one way you can tell they're gross distortions is because they're contentious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.92,0:40:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One way they're contentious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.92,0:40:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,One way they're contentious is they demean the opposite view.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.03,0:40:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, in a debating class, each person presents his side, and he presents his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.98,0:40:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In that which is contentious, you don't present your side, you attack their side, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.13,0:40:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a different approach altogether, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.07,0:40:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't care whether anybody agrees with anything I say whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.90,0:40:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I care?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.00,0:40:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you want to influence other people?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.09,0:40:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a parade?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.53,0:41:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Make speeches on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.55,0:41:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would anybody want to control anybody else, control what they think, control what
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.34,0:41:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they believe?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.34,0:41:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure these people believe that what they're doing is for God when they blow up a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.78,0:41:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,airplane full of innocent passengers.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.71,0:41:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They probably felt virtuous as they killed 3,000 in the Twin Towers.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.96,0:41:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Pearl Harbor only killed 2,000 in 2400.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.07,0:41:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Pearl Harbor only killed 2,400.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.80,0:41:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a military target.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.80,0:41:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Twin Towers killed 3,000, not military target, innocent civilians, blown up without
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.21,0:42:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,any chance to prepare for death, no confession, no absolution, no nothing, out of body, 3,000
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.76,0:42:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,innocent civilians.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.76,0:42:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see any peace parades after Pearl Harbor, nobody told me it was unintegrated
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.76,0:42:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to counter attack Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.50,0:42:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see any peace parades after Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.50,0:42:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A littleTIN.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.48,0:42:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why no?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.48,0:42:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.67,0:42:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if we calibrate the level of truth of that particular distortion of truth, we see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.78,0:42:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.63,0:42:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,190 is putting one's own ego above the reality of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.44,0:42:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.44,0:42:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the reason it's below 200 is because it's a denial of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.23,0:42:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the left end is characterized, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.73,0:42:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucifer is characterized by arrogance.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.15,0:42:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrogance and remorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.15,0:42:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,replacing facts with opinions and by distorting the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.51,0:42:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,distorting the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.50,0:43:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the difference between Luciferic and Satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.50,0:43:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,One form of the Luciferic is to distort truth
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.26,0:43:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you cannot tell good from evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.96,0:43:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In our society, many people cannot tell good from evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.15,0:43:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,One side of conflict is demonic, calibrates at 70,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.15,0:43:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and frankly, after it's juiced you, it will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.75,0:43:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So people parade to the defense of that energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.17,0:43:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Lenin said they're useful idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.55,0:43:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Lenin was the one that introduced terrorism
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.63,0:43:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as a legitimate way of achieving one's goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.48,0:43:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Lenin that popularized terrorism
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.65,0:43:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.73,0:43:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who supported his position,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.15,0:44:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he called them useful idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.13,0:44:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And after the revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.94,0:44:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they're the first ones to be extinguished.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.13,0:44:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The first ones you're gonna execute after the revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.76,0:44:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because if a person is not aligned with their own origins,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.19,0:44:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,if they don't respect their father and mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.94,0:44:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,their own culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.11,0:44:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they turn against their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.44,0:44:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If they turn against their own, you can't trust them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.28,0:44:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So after the revolution, you kill them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.94,0:44:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The first people extinguished after a revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.03,0:44:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,are the revolutionaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.21,0:44:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellectual revolutionaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.65,0:44:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who sell out their own integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.59,0:44:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for the gain of being superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.51,0:44:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So Stalin said he called them useful idiots,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.63,0:44:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and after the revolution, they're all shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.59,0:44:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So they don't bring about freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.59,0:44:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they bring about their own execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.21,0:45:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The devotion to the truth, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.15,0:45:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,means the willingness to look at some painful facts of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.36,0:45:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Painful facts of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.96,0:45:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The ostrich head in the sand,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.50,0:45:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is a wimp. The wimp is unable to look at the downside of human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.88,0:45:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen don't read other gentleman's mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.59,0:45:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't other gentleman's mail he was reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.71,0:45:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese were planning Pearl Harbor
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.71,0:45:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and the destruction of the United States influence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.71,0:45:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the entire Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.71,0:45:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And kill as many Americans as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.67,0:45:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see in the interacting balance of power
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.75,0:45:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,how these levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.75,0:45:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which tend to manifest in various places geographically
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.75,0:45:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,force certain moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.07,0:45:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how the victim forces the perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.07,0:45:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim forces the perpetrator
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.96,0:46:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to take action against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.78,0:46:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Suicide by police is the name of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.78,0:46:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The second atomic bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.80,0:46:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,after World War II
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.80,0:46:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,was forced upon themselves by Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.36,0:46:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't get the implication
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.78,0:46:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that a second atomic bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.78,0:46:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that doesn't stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.01,0:46:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They forced a second atomic bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.01,0:46:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,before they got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.01,0:46:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that stupid or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.48,0:46:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The two atomic bombs they get
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.48,0:46:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that the war is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.48,0:46:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have met our master.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.03,0:46:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.03,0:46:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We awaken the sleeping giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.03,0:46:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you wake up the sleeping giant
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.03,0:46:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the game is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.21,0:46:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we looked at this morning at the realities of war and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.30,0:46:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We use consciousness research to find,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.30,0:46:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to the core
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.30,0:46:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is the truth of these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.01,0:47:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to get to the truth of it is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.01,0:47:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,being personal about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.01,0:47:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have any position about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.01,0:47:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if this side is right or that side is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.03,0:47:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's immaterial.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.03,0:47:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because where I live all that is just nonsensical drama anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.03,0:47:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the games of the ego out there
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.03,0:47:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm not the ego and neither are you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.40,0:47:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So who cares about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.55,0:47:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody wants to kill each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.55,0:47:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.55,0:47:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should you interfere?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.55,0:47:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should you interfere?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.09,0:47:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People get a wallop
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.44,0:47:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,by killing themselves and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.44,0:47:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.03,0:47:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.03,0:47:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know that it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.03,0:47:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know that it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.84,0:47:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We have historically, I always go back to history
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.84,0:47:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you don't learn from history
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.84,0:47:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to repeat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.84,0:48:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with the Russians of course
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.84,0:48:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is they had no knowledge of ways of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.84,0:48:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How to hold title to a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.84,0:48:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you buy a house?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.84,0:48:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you open a bank account?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.84,0:48:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean checking account?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.84,0:48:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean mortgage?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.84,0:48:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They had no idea what we're even talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.84,0:48:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It made no sense to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.76,0:48:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So generally what you have then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.76,0:48:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when you remove a fascist regime
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.76,0:48:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is you have a period of political unrest
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.76,0:48:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and instability and chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.76,0:48:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the warring factions come out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.21,0:48:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The communists will try to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.21,0:48:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The fascists will try to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.21,0:48:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The different religious factions
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.21,0:48:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,will try to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.21,0:48:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I expect chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.21,0:48:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine it's going to be a mess for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.21,0:48:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because our idea of living with those who differ from us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.40,0:48:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget it took us hundreds of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.40,0:48:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,America was old by the time
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.59,0:48:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we even settled blacks and whites, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.59,0:48:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was young
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.71,0:48:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the blacks had their own bathrooms and bus stations.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.71,0:49:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just as a kid thought that's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.71,0:49:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that's the way it is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.94,0:49:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because black people are poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.94,0:49:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think it was because they were black.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.94,0:49:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought in terms of black and white.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.94,0:49:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought that they must be poor
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.94,0:49:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that they don't have washstands that work.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.94,0:49:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The toilets don't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.11,0:49:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the filling station was dilapidated
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.11,0:49:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that they used.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.11,0:49:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the white man's
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.11,0:49:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,either was all about money, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.30,0:49:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it took us hundreds of years
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.30,0:49:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to even settle that simple an issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.30,0:49:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Catholics and the Protestants
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.30,0:49:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,warred for thousands of, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.30,0:49:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand years, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.30,0:49:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They're still at it in Northern Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.88,0:49:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So even a society
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.88,0:49:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at 400, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.03,0:49:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes it hundreds of years to settle out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.03,0:49:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would guess Iraq will
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.03,0:49:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,settle out in four or five hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.03,0:49:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, those factions have been at it
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.09,0:49:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for thousands of years already.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.09,0:49:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They all hate each other with a vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.09,0:49:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all coming out of the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.09,0:49:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the Palestinians kill a busload of kids
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.15,0:50:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the Israelis
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.15,0:50:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,kill a busload of pregnant mothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.15,0:50:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the more pathetic the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.15,0:50:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to answer that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.82,0:50:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we're going to have to break for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.94,0:50:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.36,0:50:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll answer it this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.46,0:50:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,From my general knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.71,0:50:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the evolution of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.78,0:50:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which I went into somewhat in the last book
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.78,0:50:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and which we'll go into more in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.78,0:50:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.78,0:50:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,since the beginning of time
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.78,0:50:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,has been an upward trajectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.78,0:50:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And at a certain point,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.94,0:50:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say the accumulated positive karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.94,0:50:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the karmic merit
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.15,0:50:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind has earned it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.15,0:50:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the right to go over 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.57,0:50:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic merit has evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.57,0:51:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because, you see, at the time of Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.57,0:51:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of mankind was 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.67,0:51:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of Jesus Christ, it was 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.76,0:51:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,By the 1600s, it was up to 185,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.76,0:51:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you saw it at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.86,0:51:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I came into this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.86,0:51:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,190 ran everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.32,0:51:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly in the late 80s,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.32,0:51:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it jumps to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.32,0:51:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, what's significant about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.40,0:51:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you're on the other side of the,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.40,0:51:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you're on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.98,0:51:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So on a ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.98,0:51:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I steer the ship
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.98,0:51:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a half a degree off,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.98,0:51:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and the compass doesn't seem like much.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.98,0:51:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But a half a degree
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.98,0:51:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,after a day or two of sailing
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.98,0:51:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,across the Pacific Ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.98,0:51:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a couple hundred miles off.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.36,0:51:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So just a few degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.36,0:51:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,makes the difference between success and failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.36,0:51:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as I say, the reason you see
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.36,0:51:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of non-integrity surfacing in Ron,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.36,0:51:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're going to get to that this afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.36,0:51:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,big corporations falling,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.42,0:52:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,congressmen being nailed
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.42,0:52:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for dishonesty and stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.42,0:52:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is because 207 will not tolerate
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.42,0:52:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that degree of non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.42,0:52:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,190, we said, business is business.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.42,0:52:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Steal a little, just don't make it too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.07,0:52:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And 207 now calls for a different action.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.51,0:52:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I had a housekeeper many years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.76,0:52:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and she used to do the shopping for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.00,0:52:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would then later check with the grocery,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.25,0:52:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and she padded the bill 10%.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.86,0:52:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I figured, so it's 10%.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.86,0:52:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't fire her.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.86,0:52:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She padded it a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.86,0:52:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I know she's running about 10%.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.86,0:52:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd tell me the groceries were $22,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.86,0:52:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and actually they're only $18.90.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.86,0:52:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So I figured, she's only stealing 10%,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.86,0:52:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so I never said anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.86,0:52:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you'd feel you have to say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.07,0:53:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just sweep everything under the rug anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.15,0:53:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now integrity would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.30,0:53:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have to tell her,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.30,0:53:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,listen, you're going 10% on top of the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.82,0:53:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I may negotiate with her and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.15,0:53:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,look, if you want a 10% raise,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.15,0:53:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me, and I'll give you 10% more.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.15,0:53:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've got to get myself out of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.15,0:53:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm going to be non-integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.15,0:53:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if I don't call her on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.15,0:53:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,At 190, I'd say, look,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.36,0:53:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,she's only stealing 10%.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.36,0:53:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.36,0:53:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Good housekeepers are hard to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.36,0:53:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I've got to live with that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.36,0:53:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because I realize there's a karmic consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.36,0:53:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to saying okay to non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.36,0:53:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.53,0:53:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.53,0:53:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So eat well because this afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.53,0:53:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to hit business.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.53,0:54:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A difficult morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.03,0:54:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Only a couple of deaths along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.88,0:54:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody got outraged with what I had to say
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.98,0:54:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and left enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.98,0:54:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I consider that a great blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.98,0:54:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To try and contextualize compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.63,0:54:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for all positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.63,0:54:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To be compassionate for your enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.36,0:54:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who is walking under some kind of an understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.67,0:54:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,just as you're walking under some kind of an understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.67,0:54:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure on some other plane,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.15,0:54:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,some other day, we'll all laugh about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.15,0:54:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I've shared with you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.86,0:54:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the laughter I had with the fellow
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.86,0:54:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that I skewered with a sword and he skewered me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.09,0:54:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He did it for Allah and I did it for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.09,0:54:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I mean, we killed each other good, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.88,0:55:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember exactly both experts.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.28,0:55:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And boy, did I kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.28,0:55:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And did he ever kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.28,0:55:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We were just fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.50,0:55:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At the zen of weaponry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.50,0:55:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we both went out of body and got hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.50,0:55:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I killed him for Jesus and he killed me for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.88,0:55:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was the funniest thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.88,0:55:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that moment, you transcend your warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.03,0:55:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand the warrior?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.03,0:55:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We transcended the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.03,0:55:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was willing to die for God, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.46,0:55:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I died for Jesus and he did it for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.46,0:55:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've respected the enemy ever since
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.88,0:55:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because he's just like I am
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.96,0:55:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in some different level of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.09,0:55:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic working out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.23,0:55:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, this is the karmic theater of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.23,0:55:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.38,0:55:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How can there be such a variation?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.38,0:55:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And shouldn't the world be different than it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.38,0:55:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do without the garbage cans.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.44,0:56:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I get carried away with their beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.90,0:56:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I can't remember what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.44,0:56:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.44,0:56:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.44,0:56:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the lower right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.78,0:56:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom Lincoln sent us that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.96,0:56:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.96,0:56:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.67,0:56:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is perfect as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.67,0:56:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no intention to change it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.80,0:56:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because if this is supposed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.80,0:56:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfect school for all of us to evolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.80,0:56:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to undo bad karma, achieve new karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.80,0:56:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,then we need the whole panorama
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.46,0:56:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from the very worst to the very top.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.46,0:56:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what our world represents.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.46,0:56:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's the perfect world, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.09,0:56:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for what it is, purgatorial in nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.13,0:56:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,where else would you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.13,0:57:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.44,0:57:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,where would I have killed that guy for Jesus?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.44,0:57:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And where would he have killed me for Allah?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.44,0:57:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.44,0:57:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be someplace that tolerates this craziness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.44,0:57:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This world rewards you for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.38,0:57:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we both went out here, went out as heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.38,0:57:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We were both heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.38,0:57:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we transcended the warrior at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.38,0:57:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So each of those archetypes then represent
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.63,0:57:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary steps in the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.73,0:57:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,At one point, I didn't mean to say
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.05,0:57:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the ultimate, but it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.05,0:57:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's just the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.05,0:57:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.05,0:57:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tried to try to make clear this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.71,0:57:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and it'll carry over till this afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.71,0:57:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is the difference between authority and authoritarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.71,0:57:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a purposeful misinterpretation of authority
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.15,0:57:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as authoritarian to justify demonizing authority
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.15,0:58:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by purposely distorting it as authoritarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.55,0:58:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,dictatorial there is such a thing as true authority by virtue of the nature
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.92,0:58:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which it is it is intrinsically the authority the authority and what it
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.11,0:58:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be the cat is my cat and anything I say is not coming from the authority
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.71,0:58:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because the the authority of being that which you are psychoanalytically I always
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.84,0:58:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,viewed the fact your relationship at least amongst men the relationship you
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.90,0:58:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,had with your father will pretty much set your political position later on if
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.42,0:58:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,your father was cruel unloving at Sarah you will hate authority and be therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.26,0:58:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,against all that stands for authority big business institutions the government
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.78,0:58:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and whatever please hmm view all authority as evil and get out on a
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.01,0:59:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,bandstand and parade against authority and so authoritarian is the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.82,0:59:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,abuse of power. Authority is the true nature of power because truth is power
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.57,0:59:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and the true true authority comes from integrity. So if you had a father who was
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.67,0:59:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,fair and yet firm but loved you at the same time, you will view authority as
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.19,0:59:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,both friendly and to be respected. Patriotism is the respect, the love, the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.61,0:59:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledgement. At the same time, the limitation of society is accepted and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.11,0:59:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the police are seen as somebody who will protect you, not just, you know, somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.19,0:59:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,who in an authoritarian, abusive way unleashes the dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.48,0:59:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,against innocent victims, you see, because the victims are not innocent. You don't
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.63,1:00:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,get the police dogs released on you because you were having a peace vigil.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.28,1:00:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Takes a lot of rock throwing before you know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.82,1:00:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the police to get out the water hoses, etc. So you see the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.23,1:00:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,provocation, and you see that especially in the Middle East, where one side
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.38,1:00:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,provokes the other into action so they can then blame the other and hold the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.21,1:00:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,innocent baby in her arms as the mother cries, which they keep a whole bunch of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.28,1:00:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,those videos on hand at all times. We played first on one side and then the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.82,1:00:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,other, you see. So that's the victimization of the public by the abuse
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.96,1:00:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of the power of communication of the media to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.30,1:00:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.61,1:00:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the, bring up maudlin distortions of the reality. So how you view authority
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.36,1:00:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,then? If you hate authority because your father was cruel and authoritarian, or
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.94,1:00:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,whether your father was benign and loving and supportive at the same time demanded
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.55,1:01:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that you finish your homework. So positionality about authority then has
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.38,1:01:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,something to do with many, many things, one of them being childhood experience of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.28,1:01:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,how you were parented.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.44,1:01:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If your mother and father were unfeeling and cruel, then you'd be very hostile to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.48,1:01:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it. So our host thought a lot of people who protest authority, even in its
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.73,1:01:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,legitimate form, probably had a very bad relationship with their fathers, you know
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.84,1:01:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm saying? So there's many psychological, psychoanalytic, as well as the nature of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.80,1:01:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego itself, which tends to positionalize us and get into right and
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.59,1:01:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong. So this afternoon we're going to talk about business. Let's have business up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.51,1:01:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They say if you got through war, business will be a snap.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.05,1:01:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If this morning didn't blow you out, you'd probably be okay. Now this looks pretty, is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.38,1:02:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that readable? All right. Because of its importance to our culture, war and peace has to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.30,1:02:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,staying alive. Now that you're staying alive, how do you survive? So survival then takes
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.48,1:02:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,us into the world of a job, business, commerce, money, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.07,1:02:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.19,1:02:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,abundance, and all of those then are experienced depending on one's level of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.82,1:02:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. So we want to talk about success. There's many workshops on
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.30,1:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,success and making money, and I could never afford to go to one of them when I
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.84,1:02:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,was younger. It's 350 for the weekend, then I figure, you always say you stay
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.61,1:02:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,poor. Okay, that's great. That's all right. Everybody can cock their head a little
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.84,1:02:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,bit. We can tell who's paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.44,1:02:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's paying attention? Who ain't? That's fine. That's fine. That's good. That's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.40,1:03:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. That's good. All right. So the demonization, the vilification of business then comes from
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.01,1:03:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the same source as that which denigrates the United States and its presidency and the flag
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.94,1:03:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and God and the Constitution and all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.94,1:03:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because business is seen as a source of power, it's hated and stigmatized, and every time,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.92,1:03:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an international business conference. They parade up and down the sidewalk with
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.67,1:03:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,signs. They hate business, and they hate big business. So I always get a kick out of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.07,1:03:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,these guys. Here he's got glasses on made by some business. He's got a shirt on made
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.53,1:03:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,by some business. He's got pants on made by some business. His shoes were made by some
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.21,1:04:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,business. His watch, he's looking at his business-made watch, standing on a business-made
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.48,1:04:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sidewalk while he holds a business-made placard made out of business-made things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.96,1:04:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, it's business. Well, okay. So now, when you croak, what are they going
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.38,1:04:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to put you in? Because business makes caskets, too. You know what I'm saying? So we have
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.19,1:04:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept that and see business for what it is. The corporate culture, you know, is really
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.28,1:04:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the out-picturing of abundance. People talk about abundance. Well, here it is. Here we
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.53,1:04:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,are in this magnificent room, magnificent carpet, all kinds of electronic equipment.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.21,1:04:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.59,1:04:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.65,1:04:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.65,1:04:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's sort of stupid to sit here and vilify business when my whole survival
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.36,1:05:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,from moment to moment is dependent on business, isn't it? Without business, there'd be
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.34,1:05:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,no electric. We would all be sitting here in the dark. You wouldn't hear any of my voice,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.78,1:05:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and none of us would have anything on.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.78,1:05:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the alternative to that is to live in a cave and spin your own clothes. And if anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.78,1:05:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to try that lifestyle, you have the severe ascetic, I'll tell you, it's cold in
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.28,1:05:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,cold in winter and it's hot in summer. No. So, what industry and business represent is
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.42,1:05:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective enterprise. It's the collective abundance of all of us. The total business
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.38,1:05:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,output of America belongs to all of us. Now, technically, you may be only legally entitled
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.71,1:05:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to this little piece of stock or whatever, but you get, we all get the benefit of the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.92,1:05:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it. And to say, how much of it do I own, you're coming from the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.17,1:05:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can all walk in here for free. It doesn't cost you anything to walk into
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.38,1:05:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,this hotel and walk around and go to the men's room and walk out on the sidewalk. All of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.63,1:06:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that costs millions of dollars. So, from moment to moment, we all benefit by an infinite trillions
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.78,1:06:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of dollars of productive output of our society. So, when you vilify industry and business,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.86,1:06:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're vilifying yourself because that's your own energy pouring out there and that's
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.76,1:06:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of your survival. Without penicillin, you're going to be dead. Without a hospital
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.88,1:06:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to when you have a heart attack, you're going to stop breathing and stay right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.28,1:06:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Without an ambulance to come and get you, without an oxygen tank. So, every single instant,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.26,1:06:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you are benefi-, benefiting by the total output of the industriousness and integrity of the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.05,1:06:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,society.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.05,1:06:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've inherited a certain momentum from our previous generation. So, the previous
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.15,1:07:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,generation already had Model A Fords, Model T Fords. We had a 29 Model A Ford Roadster
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.55,1:07:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with a rumble seat. It was fantastic, but it wasn't a streamliner. So, in the 30s, when
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.96,1:07:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the first streamliner car came out, and also the railroad, you know, we had the old locomotive.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.15,1:07:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then the streamliner, the Hiawatha came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.00,1:07:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the train went by once a day, 4 o'clock. We lived on the sticks. So, we'd take our
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.98,1:07:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,bicycles and drive a couple of miles and we'd wait until 4 o'clock. And the Hiawatha would
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.76,1:07:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,come through. That was the high point of our day and then the, then it was gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.42,1:07:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, the hard work of all of us, generation after generation then, we collect a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.15,1:07:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,amount of capital behind us. The accumulated infrastructure of our society, the amount
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.48,1:07:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of money we make is a free gift. Sidewalks don't cost you anything. They're paid for
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.26,1:07:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by your parents and your grandparents. The automobile industry has already worked itself
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.88,1:08:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to death to produce the car that you just walk in. You can buy a better used one now
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.40,1:08:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,for practically nothing than you could buy brand new .
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.17,1:08:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, everyone benefits by the total collective output of all of us. Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.15,1:08:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we should reauthenticate it, reappreciate it, and re-contextualize the value and building
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.21,1:08:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But the importance of that to all of our survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.09,1:08:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We as a nation are enormously productive, and we are like a bastion, we're like a sign
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.56,1:08:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to the rest of the world, this is what's possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.25,1:08:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what's possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.81,1:08:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we say it arose according to a certain economic system, which we would like
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.35,1:08:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to see other people incorporate.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.82,1:08:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really care whether they incorporate our free enterprise system or not, what do
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.55,1:08:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I care about it, as long as I get penicillin when I'm sick and oxygen when I can't breathe
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.02,1:09:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore and I've got a car to park, and a parking lot that somebody paid for, who paid
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.50,1:09:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for all that pavement out there?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.89,1:09:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you ride around all day on the back of corporate production and industry through
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.80,1:09:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a number of generations.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.11,1:09:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So to vilify it is sort of stupid, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.89,1:09:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,To vilify it, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.17,1:09:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can vilify it and stigmatize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.93,1:09:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,By warping it, by projecting certain misinterpretations.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.96,1:09:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The image of the victim and the perpetrator is so inculcated in our disruptive society
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.39,1:09:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,right now, it's first of all very, it makes you sound very important to stigmatize something
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.72,1:09:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and criticize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.92,1:09:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So if your self-esteem is not too high, what you do is you go about criticizing everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.18,1:10:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The government, state and federal.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.25,1:10:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The military, industry.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.59,1:10:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ford Motor Company, you name it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.73,1:10:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of this criticism comes out of distortions of Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.76,1:10:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The distortions that see authority as authoritarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.15,1:10:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That see authority as exploitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.56,1:10:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Exploitation like any judgmental thing depends on your point of view.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.43,1:10:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Ford introduced the first five dollar a day workplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.02,1:10:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Five dollars a day.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.28,1:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It was overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.68,1:10:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside of Henry Ford.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.21,1:10:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you weren't allowed to smile or go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.09,1:10:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You got paid good money,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.64,1:10:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but you weren't supposed to have a good time at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.52,1:10:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who joked around was the foreman quickly told you.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.10,1:10:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you wanted to go to the bathroom twice,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.90,1:10:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you say you went already this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.14,1:10:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked in an automobile company, a factory,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.85,1:11:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and I remember how it was with the production line.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.85,1:11:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can picture that production line any way you want to.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.89,1:11:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, when we talk about the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.82,1:11:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we're always talking about perceptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.28,1:11:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that production line my road to freedom,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.10,1:11:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or was it my road to captivity?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.46,1:11:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on your political prejudice in the matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.78,1:11:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my means of working my way through medical school
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.51,1:11:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.82,1:11:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the assembly line then was to me a road to freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.31,1:11:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say, well, the assembly line
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.53,1:11:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is symbolic.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.69,1:11:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a symbolic of captivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.69,1:11:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the captive worker who's chained to his post,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.34,1:11:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and time did go very slowly,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.34,1:11:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because this auto body would come down,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.03,1:11:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,creak, creak, creak, creak, creak, creak,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.03,1:11:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I was supposed to go bzzzt on it,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.03,1:11:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it went creak, creak, creak, creak,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.03,1:11:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,down to the next person.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.03,1:12:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you had to wait like 45 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.03,1:12:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you, that was the longest 45 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.03,1:12:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I did my bzzzt, and I had nothing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.03,1:12:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, nothing to do for 45 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.03,1:12:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my 45 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.03,1:12:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'd almost want to run over and grab that thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.03,1:12:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm here, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.30,1:12:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tedium.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.69,1:12:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so instead of demonizing industry
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.69,1:12:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and business, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.69,1:12:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say we realize that you wouldn't even exist without it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.02,1:12:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Few of the people would be alive in this room
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.02,1:12:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't for industry or business.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.14,1:12:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Industry and business is what puts out pharmaceuticals.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.14,1:12:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we don't have the plague anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.14,1:12:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's why we don't have tuberculosis anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.14,1:12:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was an intern,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.97,1:12:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,infantile paralysis was,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.97,1:12:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all these diseases were rampant,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.97,1:12:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,whooping cough and diphtheria and typhoid.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.97,1:12:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that one where your arm went weak
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.97,1:12:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you were paralyzed?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.48,1:12:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,President Roosevelt had it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.48,1:13:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Polio, yes, polio.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.18,1:13:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My job then, I was the only doctor on
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.26,1:13:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in this infectious disease hospital.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.26,1:13:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The head doctor had an alcohol problem,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.26,1:13:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and he disappeared and left it for the intern.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.26,1:13:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So here I am, an intern,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.26,1:13:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the middle of a polio epidemic,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.26,1:13:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.26,1:13:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no laboratory technician,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.26,1:13:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so the mother brings the child in.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.26,1:13:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell from across the room,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.26,1:13:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,he's got polio.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.26,1:13:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see the one side out on the kid,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.26,1:13:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can see the terror in the parent's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.26,1:13:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was by myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.27,1:13:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so I quickly ran in.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.27,1:13:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,First I was the doctor,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.27,1:13:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,then I was the lab technician.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.50,1:13:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I ran the back, and I did a spinal tap on this kid,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.50,1:13:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I spun it down in the centrifuge,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.50,1:13:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I counted, and I looked,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.50,1:13:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw all the white cells there,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.43,1:13:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had to go out and tell the parents.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.97,1:13:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They would drop dead,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.97,1:13:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,just drop over on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.97,1:14:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the father would bring us out
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.10,1:14:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was hopeless,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.25,1:14:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,hopeless paralysis.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.47,1:14:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you got up to the thoracic region,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.47,1:14:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the diaphragm, you went in an iron lung.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.89,1:14:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And life in an iron lung is not fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.39,1:14:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You lay on your back inside this iron thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.39,1:14:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't breathe when you want to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.39,1:14:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You breathe when it breathes you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.32,1:14:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And boredom, talk about boredom,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.32,1:14:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about 45 seconds waiting for the next auto body
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.32,1:14:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to come down.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.32,1:14:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You imagine spending years that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.32,1:14:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Industry and commerce has saved us from that.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.32,1:14:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us have to spend our life
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.32,1:14:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in an iron lung.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.02,1:14:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need oxygen, an ambulance will come
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.02,1:14:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring it to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.44,1:14:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Carefully trained EMTs are experts.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.44,1:14:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I've watched some EMT teams work together.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.44,1:14:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.44,1:14:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a ballet.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.44,1:14:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one just moved like they were telepathically connected.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.53,1:14:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Magical.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.69,1:14:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To save your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.69,1:14:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we owe our life to industry.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.69,1:14:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We owe certain allegiance to it,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.69,1:15:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore we owe a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.69,1:15:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,thankfulness, gratitude, and respect.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.69,1:15:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That off the backs of all these workers,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.96,1:15:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we have
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.50,1:15:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the gift of our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.50,1:15:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.88,1:15:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.22,1:15:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,business and industry needs to reinvent itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.22,1:15:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you why.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.22,1:15:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it has bought
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.22,1:15:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of the criticism against it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.22,1:15:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's incorporated the negative values.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.22,1:15:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It itself
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.48,1:15:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from guilt and apology all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.48,1:15:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive us.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.48,1:15:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,An apologetic,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.60,1:15:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,defensive, guilt-ridden,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.60,1:15:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,shame-based kind of
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.60,1:15:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of, really,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.60,1:15:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the distortions of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.05,1:15:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're integrous, and you've done the best
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.05,1:15:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you can, and you know your company's doing
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.05,1:15:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the best you can, you can look everybody in the eye
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.05,1:15:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't have to give an apology
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.05,1:15:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for anything. You can give an explanation,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.05,1:15:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't need to give any apologies.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.05,1:15:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to apologize
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.05,1:16:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for. What they're usually
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.34,1:16:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,hit with is the distortion of truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.34,1:16:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and now they have to apologize, not for
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.34,1:16:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,reality, but for some distortion of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.34,1:16:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like, when did you
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.34,1:16:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,quit beating your wife, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.34,1:16:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he never did beat his wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.01,1:16:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, the most powerful nation
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.80,1:16:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,on Earth came about as a result of
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.80,1:16:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the free enterprise system,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.80,1:16:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of which enterprise industry
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.82,1:16:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and business,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.76,1:16:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll get into
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.76,1:16:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,some of these examples.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.35,1:16:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the people who denigrate
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.35,1:16:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,our form of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.35,1:16:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,hate capitalism, hate the free market system,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.35,1:16:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,hate the presidency,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.35,1:16:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,hate all that, I notice that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.35,1:16:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't move.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.35,1:16:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, why
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.89,1:16:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,are you still here, freako?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.89,1:16:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like Gonsaville,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.98,1:16:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,why are you still living in Gonsaville?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.98,1:16:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the positive payoff
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.38,1:16:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of living in America is so tremendous
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.38,1:16:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that people are willing to die to get here,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.38,1:17:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and they cross the Mexican border,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.38,1:17:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,they die by the hundreds every year,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.47,1:17:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to the land of free enterprise,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.47,1:17:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which everybody else ungratefully
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.47,1:17:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and non-integrously
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.47,1:17:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is busy attacking and trying to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.47,1:17:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,denigrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.85,1:17:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My feeling is that business
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.85,1:17:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and industry should recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.85,1:17:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,itself to itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.85,1:17:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't even realize to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.89,1:17:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.43,1:17:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody has to tell them.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.43,1:17:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Without you, practically everybody in this room
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.43,1:17:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,would be dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.02,1:17:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the days of industry, the average age of death
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.02,1:17:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,was like 45 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.98,1:17:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there was nothing to keep you alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.98,1:17:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There were no pharmaceuticals, there were no
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.98,1:17:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,diagnostic, there was no x-rays,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.98,1:17:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no bacteriologic laboratories,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.92,1:17:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no hospitals.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.92,1:17:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Without industry, just about everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.92,1:17:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,would be dead, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.92,1:17:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The death rate in childbirth
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.88,1:17:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,amongst women was a third.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.88,1:17:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A third of women died in childbirth
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.88,1:18:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,due to puerperal fever.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.93,1:18:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There were no antibiotics,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.93,1:18:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,no sterilization procedures.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.46,1:18:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So the medical industry then came forth
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.46,1:18:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,with all ways to save
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.61,1:18:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,human life from suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.61,1:18:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as disfigurement
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.61,1:18:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and death.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.61,1:18:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The average healthy, reasonable
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.68,1:18:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,human being lives to be
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.68,1:18:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what, 80 now?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.68,1:18:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.26,1:18:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When I grew up, 65 you retired
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.67,1:18:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and at 66 or 67
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.67,1:18:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you had your heart attack
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.67,1:18:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.89,1:18:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true, everybody retired at 65
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.89,1:18:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and they had a heart attack within the first few years.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.89,1:18:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The average age of death
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.89,1:18:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,was around 67, 68.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.22,1:18:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have been dead 10 years already
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.22,1:18:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and more.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.94,1:18:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,To respect then
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.10,1:18:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the American public should respect
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.10,1:18:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the very source of its own affluence
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.10,1:18:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of trying to attack it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.10,1:19:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and denigrate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.35,1:19:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To do this, corporate America has to
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.35,1:19:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,understand its own value to the world
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.35,1:19:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and to each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.73,1:19:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.73,1:19:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of human life
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.73,1:19:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as it expresses itself
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.73,1:19:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in business and commerce
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.73,1:19:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which is, after all,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.73,1:19:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,at least eight hours of most people's day
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.73,1:19:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,five days a week
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.73,1:19:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in that world.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.73,1:19:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world that you denigrate and hate
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.73,1:19:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,your life is going to be miserable.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.73,1:19:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to value
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.14,1:19:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of our own work
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.14,1:19:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of that business
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.14,1:19:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to society.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.59,1:19:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say we need to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.59,1:19:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the significance of corporate America
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.59,1:19:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.55,1:19:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To do that, you have to first of all
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.55,1:19:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,look more at the context
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.55,1:19:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,than the content.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.06,1:19:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of times business makes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.06,1:19:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,actually horrendous mistakes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.06,1:19:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of this apologist, defensive attitude
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.06,1:20:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,partly due to the trial lawyers association
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.06,1:20:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and various other things.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.06,1:20:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But, hmm
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.18,1:20:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've watched a lot of really painful disasters
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.18,1:20:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore I always recommend
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.18,1:20:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,first understand who you really are to the world
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.18,1:20:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and stop being apologetic.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.18,1:20:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop being guilt ridden
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.50,1:20:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because you make profits.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.85,1:20:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Who gets the profits of business?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.85,1:20:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The country gets the profits of business.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.77,1:20:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm a multi-billionaire
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.77,1:20:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't put it in a coffee can
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.77,1:20:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in my backyard
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.77,1:20:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I put it in some industry.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.77,1:20:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I put it in a bank.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.31,1:20:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And that capital goes back out into the world
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.31,1:20:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to be
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.47,1:20:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of use for making
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.47,1:20:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,building universities and things.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.47,1:20:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get old and guilty
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.47,1:20:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you can start a society
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.47,1:20:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a beneficial society
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.47,1:20:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but during
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.59,1:20:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,our lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.59,1:20:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,does anybody keep their money in the mattress here?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.59,1:20:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody hide it in the mattress?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.59,1:21:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All your dirty capital
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.10,1:21:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've accumulated
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.10,1:21:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you rotten capitalists
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.10,1:21:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you keep it in a coffee can in the backyard.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.10,1:21:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here keep your money
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.10,1:21:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in a coffee can in the backyard?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.10,1:21:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.10,1:21:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody keep it under the mattress?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.55,1:21:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.55,1:21:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody chop it up and flush it down the toilet?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.55,1:21:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.77,1:21:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the money goes right back
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.77,1:21:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it flows right back out.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.77,1:21:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nominally yours, nominally.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.77,1:21:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Functionally it's not yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.10,1:21:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you put it in the bank
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.10,1:21:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really the bank's isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.10,1:21:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The bank decides what it's going to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.10,1:21:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here where I live
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.10,1:21:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to start a new 125
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.10,1:21:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,house development project.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.10,1:21:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to cost millions and millions of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.10,1:21:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got to run water, basic things,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.10,1:21:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,electric, all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.73,1:21:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we need is
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.42,1:21:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a consciousness coach.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.42,1:21:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the word coach is sort of over abused
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.42,1:22:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in business and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.42,1:22:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need a better word than consciousness coach
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.42,1:22:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but frankly that's what they need.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.47,1:22:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody to re-contextualize back
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.47,1:22:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all to the company
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.47,1:22:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as a whole
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.47,1:22:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,with the executives and the people
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.47,1:22:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that interface with the public.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.47,1:22:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't mean public relations people
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.47,1:22:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're a lot of times idiots.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.47,1:22:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're worse than anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.73,1:22:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're a lot in their 20s and they're abrasive.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.73,1:22:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They put out advertisements
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.73,1:22:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that make you disgusted.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.73,1:22:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That cracking duck.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.02,1:22:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't shut up that cracking duck.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.02,1:22:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate Affleck.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.02,1:22:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I really hate Affleck.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.25,1:22:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there's a guy, a new TV commercial
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.25,1:22:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this guy can't get his computer to work
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.25,1:22:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so he screams at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.38,1:22:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But the sound of screaming
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.38,1:22:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,if you calibrate the sound of screaming
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.38,1:22:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's way down low.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.27,1:22:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Loud cracking ducks it's way down low.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.06,1:22:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Affleck I telepathically communicated
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.06,1:22:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with Affleck and I said
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.06,1:23:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,oh god this is awful fellas.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.57,1:23:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I really did sort of hold a
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.57,1:23:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,corrective view of the duck.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.98,1:23:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I do notice that
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.98,1:23:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the duck now comes on
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.98,1:23:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's much quieter.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.42,1:23:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get more customers
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.46,1:23:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with a happy quiet duck
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.46,1:23:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,than an abrasive one.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.22,1:23:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Affleck was coming to
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.22,1:23:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the girls ranch where I'm at
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.22,1:23:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're providing the health insurance
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.22,1:23:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said I don't want to see the guy
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.72,1:23:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when he comes here.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.72,1:23:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I hate Affleck.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.97,1:23:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm talking about more seriously
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.97,1:23:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is the awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.18,1:23:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you see they get backed up against the corner
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.18,1:23:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and they come out of guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.18,1:23:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they start using deception.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.53,1:23:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we found out with consciousness research
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.53,1:23:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.27,1:23:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask this
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.27,1:23:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of this crowd.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.17,1:24:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconsciously everybody knows
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.00,1:24:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're being lied to.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.00,1:24:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconsciously everybody knows
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.67,1:24:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're being lied to.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.67,1:24:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.67,1:24:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the company executive
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.64,1:24:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the CEO gets on TV
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.64,1:24:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and then stonewalls
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.64,1:24:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and flatly lies
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.64,1:24:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is fooling nobody at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.06,1:24:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So this recalls a couple of
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.06,1:24:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,painful interviews.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.47,1:24:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In as much as that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.47,1:24:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,like defeat on plump juicy
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.47,1:24:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,innocent things
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.18,1:24:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we can say that a successful corporation
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.18,1:24:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically draws to itself enemies
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.18,1:24:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of its success
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.18,1:24:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,out of envy and sheer hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.18,1:24:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which is integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.56,1:24:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So Sam Walton and I
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.44,1:24:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,used to correspond and of course I calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.44,1:24:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,his principles and we calibrated Walmart
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.44,1:24:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that. And as we said last time
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.44,1:24:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we predicted in 95 what would be
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.44,1:24:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and sure enough Walmart turned out to be
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.44,1:25:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the biggest corporation in America
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.44,1:25:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,built on integrous principles.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.47,1:25:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Proof that integrity pays on the bottom line.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.47,1:25:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well Sam Walton died
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.38,1:25:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and Walmart calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.97,1:25:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,around 380 I think when
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.97,1:25:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he was alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.97,1:25:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dropped to maybe 15 or 20 points since then
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.97,1:25:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.27,1:25:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the next president came up was black
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.27,1:25:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and I watched the most painful interview on TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.27,1:25:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time those who like
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.56,1:25:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to attack big business and find something wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.56,1:25:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,were attacking Walmart
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.56,1:25:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that they were employing child labor
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.56,1:25:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in third world countries.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.56,1:25:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They were like the dirty old
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.56,1:25:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,men thriving off
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.19,1:25:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,these poor little children's
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.19,1:25:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,work and sweat and labor.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.19,1:25:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh boy, oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.19,1:25:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So Black gets up there
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.26,1:25:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and he defends himself
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.26,1:25:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.57,1:25:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,flat out, oh we don't do that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.00,1:25:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or some idiot like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.50,1:25:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That was really painful
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.92,1:25:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought you know I wish I had a chance
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.92,1:26:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk to this executive before he got up there
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.92,1:26:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because you look at the evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.97,1:26:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of an industrial society.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.97,1:26:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Third world countries are not industrialized yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.97,1:26:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming out of agrarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.14,1:26:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we came out of agrarian in America
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.14,1:26:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we went through the sweatshop phase.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.14,1:26:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody does.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.27,1:26:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The children in the needlework, the seamstresses
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.27,1:26:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you remember the one in Boston
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.27,1:26:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the seamstresses were all in New York City.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.27,1:26:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They were locked into their
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.34,1:26:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,factory
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.30,1:26:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with the sewing machines and they all burned to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.30,1:26:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.30,1:26:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you come out of an agrarian society
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.30,1:26:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you go through that phase of child labor
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.30,1:26:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,women laborers
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.30,1:26:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,seamstresses
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.39,1:26:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of as you move into industrialization
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.39,1:26:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so you have a phase there.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.39,1:26:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now people don't realize
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.77,1:26:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what poverty is
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.77,1:26:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and you look at some of the favelas
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.77,1:26:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,on the sides of the mountains
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.84,1:26:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in Brazil
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.89,1:26:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the big city in Brazil?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.69,1:26:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Rio.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.69,1:27:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You visit those shacks on the side of the mountain
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.69,1:27:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and you realize what poverty is.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.77,1:27:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if those children
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.77,1:27:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,could get a job at 10 cents an hour
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.77,1:27:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole family's economy
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.77,1:27:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,would jump like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.77,1:27:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They could support the whole family.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.77,1:27:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a third world country
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.89,1:27:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a need for needle trades
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.89,1:27:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the children are available
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.89,1:27:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's their phase
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.34,1:27:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of an agrarian society.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.34,1:27:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright so to support
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.75,1:27:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of a third world country
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.75,1:27:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,into an industrialized society
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.75,1:27:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,if American capital
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.90,1:27:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,like let's say Walmart
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.90,1:27:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,goes to a country like that
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.90,1:27:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and says look we'll give you
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.90,1:27:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,what to them is huge amounts of money
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.90,1:27:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to do this
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.22,1:27:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and needle work
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.22,1:27:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in return for which
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.22,1:27:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we want the children's work hours
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.22,1:27:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,limited to 8 hours
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.22,1:27:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to have fresh air
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.22,1:27:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they must still have medical coverage
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.22,1:27:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,every child must have at least 2 hours a day of school
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.22,1:27:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in a bargaining position
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.22,1:28:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you're holding the big bucks
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.22,1:28:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and they want your big bucks
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.22,1:28:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can trade business
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.30,1:28:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for humanitarian principles
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.30,1:28:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.30,1:28:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So Walmart could be the liberator
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.30,1:28:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of these exploited third world children
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.30,1:28:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they brought the whole culture up
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.30,1:28:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to abundance
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.32,1:28:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the respect for human life
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.35,1:28:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that no door should be locked
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.35,1:28:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with children in there
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.35,1:28:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in case of fire etc
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.35,1:28:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so they could have been the hero
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.35,1:28:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they could have been the savior
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.35,1:28:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of the beneficial savior
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.35,1:28:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of the exploited
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.35,1:28:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,third world children
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.35,1:28:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,instead they came on
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.48,1:28:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and stonewalled it
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.86,1:28:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to our explanations
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.86,1:28:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the Red Cross
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.89,1:28:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,did the same thing
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.89,1:28:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,New Coke did the same thing
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.89,1:28:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Coca Cola Company with the New Coke
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.89,1:28:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the bald dead disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.89,1:28:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,all these are
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.89,1:28:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,blatant examples of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.89,1:28:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,not being able to contextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.89,1:29:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the thing in such a way
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.89,1:29:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's coming from
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.89,1:29:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt and lying
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.89,1:29:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,which we just demonstrated
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.89,1:29:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.89,1:29:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody knows when they're being lied to
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.89,1:29:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so you come out rotten
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.89,1:29:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you come out rotten instead of a savior
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.89,1:29:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you vindicate
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.89,1:29:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the vilification of industry
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.89,1:29:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've just been
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.89,1:29:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,industry at its worst
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.96,1:29:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,where's our piggy
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.46,1:29:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there you have
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.46,1:29:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,American capitalism
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.46,1:29:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as viewed from the Marxist position
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.46,1:29:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,exploiting the worker
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.46,1:29:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,workers you have nothing to lose
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.46,1:29:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but your chains
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.85,1:29:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is the fate of the worker
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.69,1:29:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in Russia, China
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.69,1:29:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all the communist countries
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.07,1:29:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ok
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.80,1:29:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there you got the downside
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.80,1:29:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of capitalism
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.80,1:29:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you exploit her
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.80,1:30:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,ok
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.11,1:30:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so a coach would
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.11,1:30:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,coach people on how to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.11,1:30:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he would coach you on timing
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.78,1:30:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,this week American Airlines
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.78,1:30:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,after the union
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.78,1:30:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,settled the contract
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.94,1:30:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,then tells you that the top executives
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.94,1:30:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,are about to get 1.5 million bonuses
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.94,1:30:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that are exempt from
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.94,1:30:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what timing huh
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.94,1:30:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what timing you don't need enemies
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.94,1:30:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,when you do that against yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.94,1:30:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.94,1:30:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean stupid I mean really
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.94,1:30:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,even they realize it was really
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.94,1:30:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,dumb dumb dumb and they've retracted it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.94,1:30:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but the bad news you know
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.94,1:30:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the bad image is out there already
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.94,1:30:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's Mr. Pig out there
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.94,1:30:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,running American Airlines
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.94,1:30:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,now we'll leave Mr. Pig out hidden away
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.10,1:30:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ok
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.56,1:30:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so to recontextualize the thing
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.56,1:30:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all you got to come from truth
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.56,1:30:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to have integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.56,1:30:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody knows when you're speaking the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.56,1:31:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can come out as a big company
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.72,1:31:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and say you know that was a bad mistake
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.72,1:31:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and we learned from it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.72,1:31:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody holds you that's against you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.72,1:31:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.90,1:31:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,criticizing any past business mistakes
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.90,1:31:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that the businesses came out and said
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.90,1:31:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,well you goofed on that one
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.90,1:31:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,no because when somebody admits the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.90,1:31:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you're willing to forgive them
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.90,1:31:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when they stand there in stonewall
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.90,1:31:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and frankly lie on your face
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.90,1:31:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you lose your respect for them
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.90,1:31:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,ok so we want to integrate
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.90,1:31:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,business into the overall human
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.90,1:31:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,community
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.90,1:31:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of setting it aside
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.90,1:31:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,where it's vulnerable to attack and criticism
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.47,1:31:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,ok
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.47,1:31:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a thing I wrote about
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.47,1:31:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in power versus force
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.47,1:31:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,called critical factor analysis
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.09,1:31:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we haven't spoken about
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.09,1:31:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating the levels of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.09,1:31:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in the various aspects of business
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.09,1:31:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can calibrate the level of any corporation
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.09,1:31:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,every department in that corporation
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.09,1:31:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,all the key positions
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.11,1:31:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you can ask
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.11,1:32:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the correct calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.11,1:32:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and all this job is blank
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.85,1:32:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so you've got to find somebody that has that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.85,1:32:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of hiring somebody that doesn't have it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.85,1:32:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and then firing because they don't have it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.97,1:32:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,well you shouldn't hire them if they don't have it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.97,1:32:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we said this morning
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.97,1:32:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfect calibration for a presidency
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.97,1:32:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of the United States of America
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.97,1:32:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is 460 that's perfect
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.97,1:32:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if you ask the question
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.97,1:32:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the most perfect calibration to fulfill
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.97,1:32:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the duties of that job you get 460
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.93,1:32:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,people would say wasn't 510 better
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.93,1:32:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,no 510 is not better
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.03,1:32:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,people would say it's all idiotic
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.03,1:32:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not interested in politics
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.03,1:32:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who cares about that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.18,1:32:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,420 wouldn't be able to have the moxie
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.18,1:32:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to grab the complexity of the overall situation
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.18,1:32:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.64,1:32:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,alright you can calibrate every aspect of business
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.64,1:32:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.77,1:32:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,show its application to research
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.77,1:32:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,marketing, advertising, production
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.06,1:33:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a thing called critical factor analysis
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.06,1:33:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which I mentioned in power versus force
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.06,1:33:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,most of these corporate interactions
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.06,1:33:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are with multiple corporations
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.06,1:33:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,interacting here with the government
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.06,1:33:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,here with the public, here with sales
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.06,1:33:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,here with marketing, public image, publicity
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.06,1:33:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it's highly complex
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.14,1:33:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so how can you tell where
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.14,1:33:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,an alteration
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.53,1:33:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,can change the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.89,1:33:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in critical factor analysis
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.89,1:33:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,means in a non-linear
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.89,1:33:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because now we're out of the linear
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.89,1:33:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and into the non-linear
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.89,1:33:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the complexity is already out of the linear
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.89,1:33:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond the capacity of a computer to figure out
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.89,1:33:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the multiplicity of factors
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.89,1:33:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,now run into the millions
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.42,1:33:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you find out where in those millions
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.42,1:33:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and millions of factors
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.42,1:33:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,most of which you can't even get on a computer
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.42,1:33:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because a large percentage
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.48,1:33:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of them are coming out of the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.48,1:33:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore not available
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.48,1:33:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to put into a computer
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.81,1:33:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you tell where can we
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.81,1:33:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,touch this complex interaction
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.81,1:34:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring about a desired result
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.81,1:34:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the example
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.73,1:34:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I used in the book was a huge locomotive
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.73,1:34:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,carrying billions of
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.73,1:34:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,pounds of
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.73,1:34:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,freight behind it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.05,1:34:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,15 freight cars
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.05,1:34:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a mass, a huge staggering mass
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.05,1:34:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and a very complex
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.05,1:34:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful engine, let's say
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.05,1:34:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,two or three diesel engines
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.05,1:34:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we've seen them go by out here in Arizona
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.14,1:34:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,through the Navajo lands
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.23,1:34:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. with three locomotives
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.23,1:34:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and a mile and a half
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.23,1:34:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of freight cars
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.17,1:34:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,do you know you can stop that whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.17,1:34:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with one finger like this
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.30,1:34:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,all you have to do is know where to
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.30,1:34:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,touch the control and this entire
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.30,1:34:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,thing comes to a stop
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.02,1:34:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,one light little touch
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.02,1:34:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,less than half an ounce can stop
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.02,1:34:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this entire monster
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.02,1:34:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,get in its tracks
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.93,1:34:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the critical point
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.93,1:34:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the critical factor analysis
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.93,1:35:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,if you know where to put just a half an ounce of
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.93,1:35:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,pressure the whole system
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.93,1:35:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,changes
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.14,1:35:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so it isn't a complex thing
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.85,1:35:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,a slight shift of image
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.85,1:35:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and your entire company and its impact
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.85,1:35:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the response to society totally changes
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.85,1:35:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,just the slightest
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.18,1:35:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,implication
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.36,1:35:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you are coming from good will
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.36,1:35:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than greed already impacts
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.36,1:35:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,people quite considerably
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.39,1:35:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're concerned
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.50,1:35:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this is different than advertising
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.50,1:35:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,advertising to me is made up by
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.50,1:35:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,young people with insufficient wisdom
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.50,1:35:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to contextualize the advertising
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.50,1:35:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it has any impact
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.59,1:35:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,if you calibrate a lot of
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.59,1:35:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean the companies spend
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.59,1:35:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,enormous amounts of money on this trash advertising
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.59,1:35:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell it came out of
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.65,1:35:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,a 24 year old's idea
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.65,1:35:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of what would be cute or smart
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.65,1:35:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's losing 90% of the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.75,1:35:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because first of all
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.75,1:35:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they presume everybody out there
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.75,1:35:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is 22 years old and grew up with computers
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.75,1:35:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so the average commercial
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.75,1:36:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was like this
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.86,1:36:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say to Susan
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.86,1:36:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what are they advertising
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.86,1:36:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,how many times have I said that to you
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.38,1:36:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I said what is it they're advertising
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.38,1:36:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a cute frog and then a locomotive
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.38,1:36:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then somebody stabbing somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.38,1:36:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then some rock music and then all these flashing lights
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.38,1:36:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's gone
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.38,1:36:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying to catch the label who made it
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.38,1:36:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.78,1:36:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,there's one that says
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.78,1:36:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't actually even make anything
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.26,1:36:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we only improve things
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.26,1:36:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so why are they wasting their money on me
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.82,1:36:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if they improve tennis shoes
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.82,1:36:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but don't sell tennis shoes
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.82,1:36:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then they should be advertising to manufacturers
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.82,1:36:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to use their product
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.82,1:36:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to improve their tennis shoes
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.82,1:36:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and why am I sitting through their commercial
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.60,1:36:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't make tennis balls
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.02,1:36:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we make them better
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.02,1:36:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that's good for them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.21,1:36:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,pointless advertising
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.71,1:36:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the speed of processing information
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.71,1:37:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we see commercials
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.71,1:37:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that really grab you in the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.71,1:37:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,there are some commercials that are stunning
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.71,1:37:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,stunningly brilliant
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.71,1:37:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,stunningly poignant
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.77,1:37:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,leave a lasting message
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.77,1:37:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and totally change your image of that company
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.77,1:37:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and how you feel about it
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.02,1:37:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so American products don't belong to companies
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.02,1:37:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,they belong to America
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.02,1:37:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,when you recontextualize who you are
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.02,1:37:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,business and corporate America
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.02,1:37:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you are America
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.38,1:37:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore the lack of respect
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.38,1:37:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for the company's symbols
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.38,1:37:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to me is also outrageous
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.38,1:37:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and obviously done by 24 year olds
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.60,1:37:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,log cabin syrup is supposed to be
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.60,1:37:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in a tin log cabinet
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.31,1:37:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Aunt Jemima's pancakes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.31,1:37:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is supposed to be a nice chunky dark lady
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.10,1:37:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to see some slim blonde
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.10,1:37:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because she's been modernized to modern America
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.10,1:37:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,those things
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.10,1:37:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,those symbols have become sacred to us
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.10,1:37:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,New Coke found that out
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.39,1:37:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you mess with us and you got trouble
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.39,1:37:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so America is saying
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.39,1:38:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you mess with us and you got big trouble
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.39,1:38:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,people hate the new Coke
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.15,1:38:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't buy it
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.80,1:38:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,these people do bad enough
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.80,1:38:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they keep changing the
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.80,1:38:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,at least they stay with red white and blue
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.80,1:38:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just get used to Pepsi this way
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.80,1:38:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they turn it this way
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.18,1:38:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean why are they doing that
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.02,1:38:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so if business views itself
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.02,1:38:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as semi-sacred to the public
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.02,1:38:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we hold these things in a semi-sacred way
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.18,1:38:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I still long for the Burma shave sign
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.75,1:38:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,little shavers take it easy
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.75,1:38:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,your driving is driving me crazy
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.75,1:38:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,something like that
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.75,1:39:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the Burma shave sign
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.75,1:39:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never cared for that president's wife
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.75,1:39:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,who took down all the roadsides
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.75,1:39:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the image of beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.75,1:39:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,this is somebody rather
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.68,1:39:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,well she was a do-gooder of some kind
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.68,1:39:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,now you got to look at boring miles
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.44,1:39:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of nothingness or apartment buildings
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.44,1:39:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or something
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.44,1:39:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we used to have a big sign
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.44,1:39:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a Janssen lady swimming suit
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.82,1:39:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,thirty foot long
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.82,1:39:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,yellow swimming suit
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.82,1:39:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,life is exciting
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.34,1:39:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,well let's see
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.38,1:39:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity show itself in business
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.73,1:39:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all we know that goodwill
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.73,1:39:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is an energy
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.73,1:39:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an energy
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.73,1:39:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they either got it or they ain't
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.52,1:39:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't fake it
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.85,1:39:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,goodwill and good intention
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.85,1:39:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it then spills out into the workforce
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.85,1:39:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the workforce now
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.85,1:39:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to represent
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.10,1:39:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,who they are via their work
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.10,1:40:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.35,1:40:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.00,1:40:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,using critical factor analysis
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.00,1:40:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we show that
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.00,1:40:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,these principles
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.38,1:40:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,results in
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.38,1:40:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,benefit everywhere
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.89,1:40:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,lower
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.89,1:40:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,sick time off the job
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.89,1:40:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,lower employee turnover
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.93,1:40:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,greater productivity
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.93,1:40:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,why because
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.93,1:40:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to believe
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.93,1:40:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,your product and your company
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.93,1:40:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has to have integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.11,1:40:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for you to put forth your best
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.11,1:40:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're just punching a time clock
